# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .gitignore for the Streamlit Community Cloud deployment copy.
#
# UNLIKE a normal repo, this one MUST commit its demo data (soc_db/,
# chroma_db/, *.db) — the cloud app has NO NetWitness/VPN access and
# serves those stored incidents instead. So the databases are intentionally
# TRACKED here. Only secrets and throwaway cruft are ignored.
#
# ⚠️  The stored incidents may contain internal hostnames/users/IPs. If that
#     data is sensitive, deploy from a PRIVATE GitHub repo (Streamlit Cloud
#     supports private repos) or scrub the DB first. See DEPLOY.md.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── SECRETS — never commit (LLM key etc. go in Streamlit Cloud → Secrets) ──
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
.streamlit/secrets.toml

# ── NetWitness TLS material (on-prem/VPN only; sensitive, unused in cloud) ──
*.pem
*.cer
certs/

# ── Transient SQLite sidecars (commit the .db, not its WAL/journal) ────────
*.db-wal
*.db-shm
*.db-journal

# ── Python / editor / OS cruft ─────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.pyo
*.pyd
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.venv/
venv/
env/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.bak

# ── Redundant packaged agent copies ────────────────────────────────────────
*.zip

# ── Knowledge-graph artifacts (rebuild with /graphify) ─────────────────────
graphify-out/

# ── Regenerated at runtime (not needed in the repo) ────────────────────────
soc_reporting_agent/outputs/
soc_reporting_agent/logs/
soc_reporting_agent/runtime/
soc_investigation_agent_revised/ChromaDatabase/

# NOTE: soc_db/, chroma_db/, *.db, incident_reports/, triaged_alerts/ are
# intentionally TRACKED — they are the offline demo payload the cloud app
# reads. Do not add them here.
